bayou.tcp

Class Socks5Tunnel

  • java.lang.Object
    • bayou.tcp.Socks5Tunnel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TcpTunnel

    public class Socks5Tunnel
extends Object
implements TcpTunnel
    A TcpTunnel using SOCKS5 protocol. See RFC1928

    Username/password authentication is supported, see RFC1929.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Socks5Tunnel

        public Socks5Tunnel(TcpAddress address,
                    boolean remoteDns,
                    Supplier<Async<UserPass>> userPassSupplier)
        Create a SOCKS5 tunnel.

        If remoteDns==true, `host` in tunnelTo() is sent to the tunnel service to be resolved there; otherwise, `host` is resolved by local DNS, and the IP address is sent to the tunnel. See "ATYP" in RFC1928 §4.

        If userPassSupplier!=null, username/password authentication is supported.

      • Socks5Tunnel

      • tunnelTo

        public Async<TcpConnection> tunnelTo(TcpConnection tcpConn,
                                     String host,
                                     int port)
        Description copied from interface: TcpTunnel
        Tunnel to the remote host:port.

        The `connection` is established between the client and the tunnel service. The implementation of this method does necessary protocol dance to instruct the tunnel service to tunnel to the server (at host:port).

        When this action succeeds, the resulting TcpConnection is used by the client to communicate to the server, as if it's a direct connection. The resulting TcpConnection could be the same object as the `connection` argument.

        Specified by:
        tunnelTo in interface TcpTunnel
